The 82 books that top business leaders couldn’t put down this year
What do some of the world’s most important business leaders want from a book right now? The same thing most of us want: understanding, hope and a dose of escapism.

Our annual survey of CEOs, entrepreneurs, politicians, philanthropists and other newsmakers highlights everything from nonfiction writing about managing colleagues to history books on the kings of England to more personal works of fiction.
